    "id": "ddx-5ca2b0af",
    "title": "beads: sort ready queues by queue-rank within priority",
    "description": "PROBLEM\nFEAT-004 and SD-004 now require `queue-rank` to order ready beads within a priority bucket, but the store still ignores queue-rank. Operators currently have to change `priority` to force a bead to the top, which changes urgency semantics and can reorder unrelated work.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-beads.md:104-119 defines canonical ready-queue ordering as priority, queue-rank, created_at, id, and says queue-rank must not cross priority or bypass execution filters.\n- docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-004-beads-tracker.md:196-209 defines the same deterministic queue derivation and numeric compatibility rules.\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go:1346-1355 exposes Ready and ReadyExecution, but both delegate to readyFiltered without queue-rank-specific behavior.\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go:1702-1711 sorts only by Priority, CreatedAt, and ID.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add a small queue-rank parser/helper in cli/internal/bead (acceptable names: QueueRank, queueRank, or parseQueueRank) that accepts integer values and numeric strings from Bead.Extra[\"queue-rank\"].\n- Update sortBeadsForQueue to sort by priority asc, explicit queue-rank asc with missing rank after explicit rank inside the same priority, created_at asc, then id asc.\n- Keep ReadyExecution filtering unchanged: blocked, cooldown, superseded, execution-eligible=false, and epic-only beads must be excluded before sorting.\n- Add focused store tests in cli/internal/bead/gaps_test.go or queue-specific test file.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not add queue-rank as a Bead struct field or known schema field.\n- Do not implement `ddx bead queue` CLI commands in this bead.\n- Do not change priority validation, dependency semantics, or claim semantics.",
    "acceptance": "1. TestReadySortsByQueueRankWithinPriority verifies an explicit lower `queue-rank` sorts before unranked and higher-ranked beads of the same priority.\n2. TestReadyExecutionSortsByQueueRankWithinPriority verifies ReadyExecution uses the same queue-rank order after execution-ready filtering.\n3. TestQueueRankDoesNotCrossPriorityBoundary verifies a ranked P1 bead never sorts before an unranked P0 bead.\n4. TestQueueRankMissingSortsAfterExplicitRankWithinPriority verifies missing queue-rank sorts after explicit ranks in the same priority bucket.\n5. TestQueueRankNumericStringCompatibility verifies numeric-string queue-rank values are read compatibly.\n6. WIRED-IN: sortBeadsForQueue, used by Ready and ReadyExecution, calls the queue-rank helper before created_at/id tie-breakers.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... -run \"TestReady.*QueueRank|TestQueueRank\" -count=1 passes.\n8. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... passes.\n9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.",
